n a fixed margin of error) of an "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"H3"}]},{"type":"text","value":" index using a few bitwise operations ("},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"h3ToParent"}]},{"type":"text","value":"). It is also possible to determine all the children of a parent "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"H3"}]},{"type":"text","value":" index ("},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"h3ToChildren"}]},{"type":"text","value":"). Approximate containment only applies when truncating the precision of an "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"H3"}]},{"type":"text","value":" index. The borders of hexagons indexed at a specific resolution are not approximate."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"align":"center"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"src":"/images/parent-child.png","style":"width:400px"},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"i","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A parent hexagon approximately contains seven children"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hierarchical containment allows for use cases like making contiguous sets of hexagons "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"compact"}]},{"type":"text","value":". It is then possible to "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"uncompact"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to the same input set of hexagons."}]},{"type":"text","